##1868 The Asia Minor Screw Steamship Company test

Captain Bel's Asia Minor Screw Steamship Company operated from Smyrna. This was a British enterprise. 
(Captain John W. Bell reside at Prestwick near Ayr in Scotland.)

The Company conveyed letters between various seaports in the Levant at which the ships touched, 
thus providing a British counterpart to the Russian navigation and Commerce Company and the official 
Imperial Ottoman Admiralty Steamship Postal Service. 

The Asia Minor Company seems to have had a special interest in Cyprus, and like the other two it provided its own
adhesive stamps or rather, labels from 1868 onwards.




